reviews.text: Another wonderful little rural train station in  Suffolk being Newmarket station located on a branch line between Ipswich and Cambridge easily accessible in town with a 10 minute walk to town centre

It's a sweet, quiet, simple, bit charming train station. There's not much there, not even a building, bit at least a small shelter. Not many trains pass through, and while waiting for one it can feel like time stands still.

This station is just so bad. There's too few trains to Cambridge and back, the trains are always late, and the trains are always packed to the brim when/if it does arrive. This is my only route to work and so it hugely affects me when the train is delayed by 20 minutes again.. It's also impossible to read the sign after any rain to see when the next train is due to arrive. It's ridiculous, and as I write this, I'm currently standing on the train, wedged in like sardines, and delayed as usual.
All right, but... Famous town like this deserves more character here...
Small town not far from Cambridge. Main street is a debacle when theres traffic but it has lots of options for food and clothes. Taxi stands at night time take a while.
